Lathyrus hirsutus

   [7157.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
   Synonyms
   Common names caley pea, hairy bitter vetch, ch√≠caro hirsuto, pea -
   caley
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 7157

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Kernick M 1961 pp 266
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 174 [USE]
   Duke J 1981 pp 106-107 [DRA, TEXT, RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Winter annual legume, growing 150-210 days. In the United States the
   legume is usually sown in October-November, and it flowers in early
   April.
   COMMON NAMES
   Rough pea, Caley pea, Singletary, Wild winter pea.
   FURTHER INF
   Rough pea is native of southern Europe and southwestern Asia. Growing
   45 centimetre high. Can become a weed.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
